{#-
  ContextMenu — DropdownMenu's twin, opened by right-click (`contextmenu`
  event) at the pointer coordinates instead of click on a visible trigger.

  Composes Popover (positioning + animation + dismiss) AND DropdownMenu
  (role="menu" + role="menuitem" + roving tabindex + Arrow nav +
  Enter/Space activation + close-on-item + tab-out dismiss). The
  context-menu controller adds:

    1. `contextmenu` event listener on the `area` element (default: the
       wrap itself; `parent` / `window` / a CSS selector also accepted).
       On fire, `event.preventDefault()` suppresses the native browser
       context menu in that region — accept the trade-off, document it
       (loss of native back/forward/inspect inside the area).
    2. Phantom trigger — a 0×0 `<span>` positioned `position: fixed` at
       (`event.clientX`, `event.clientY`) at the moment of contextmenu.
       Floating UI computes the popover position relative to this phantom,
       so all the existing flip / shift / autoUpdate logic from Popover
       applies unchanged. ZERO modification to the locked-in Popover code.

  Per WAI-ARIA APG "Menu (right-click)" doctrine: same keyboard / SR
  semantics as DropdownMenu — `role="menu"` + `role="menuitem"` items,
  Arrow Up/Down (cyclic) + Home/End + Enter/Space + Esc.

  Parameters:
    htmlId      (string, optional) — auto-generated. Stamped on content.
    area        (string, optional) — 'self' (default) | 'parent' | 'window'
                                     | a CSS selector.
                                     Where right-clicks open the menu.
    placement   (string, optional) — Floating UI placement (default
                                     'bottom-start' — typical context-menu
                                     idiom: open down-and-to-inline-start
                                     of the click point).
    offset      (int, optional)    — gap from the phantom trigger in px
                                     (default 0 — touches the click point).
    className   (string, optional) — extra classes on the wrap.

  Blocks:
    items (required) — N Item.html.twig embeds (with `as: 'div'`) and
                       optional `<hr class="cremona-dropdown-menu__separator">`
                       dividers + `<div class="cremona-dropdown-menu__group-label">`
                       labels. The dropdown-menu controller stamps
                       role="menuitem" + tabindex on each automatically.
-#}

{%- set htmlId    = htmlId    | default('cremona-context-menu-' ~ random()) -%}
{%- set area      = area      | default('self') -%}
{%- set placement = placement | default('bottom-start') -%}
{%- set offset    = offset    | default(0) -%}
{%- set className = className | default('') -%}

{%- set _classes = ['cremona-popover', 'cremona-dropdown-menu', 'cremona-context-menu'] -%}
{%- if className %}{%- set _classes = _classes | merge([className]) -%}{%- endif -%}

{%- set contextMenuHtmlId = htmlId -%}

<div
  class="{{ _classes | join(' ') }}"
  data-controller="popover dropdown-menu context-menu"
  data-action="contextmenu->context-menu#openAt keydown.esc@window->popover#close keydown->dropdown-menu#keydown click->dropdown-menu#onItemClick"
  data-popover-placement-value="{{ placement }}"
  data-popover-offset-value="{{ offset }}"
  data-popover-open-value="false"
  data-context-menu-area-value="{{ area }}"
>
  <span
    class="cremona-context-menu__phantom"
    data-popover-target="trigger"
    data-context-menu-target="phantom"
    aria-hidden="true"
  ></span>

  <div
    id="{{ htmlId }}"
    class="cremona-popover__content cremona-dropdown-menu__content cremona-context-menu__content"
    data-popover-target="content"
    data-state="closed"
    data-placement="{{ placement }}"
    role="menu"
    hidden
  >
    {%- block items -%}{%- endblock -%}
  </div>
</div>
